<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In May 2020, Hertz Global Holdings Inc. filed =
for bankruptcy. Then its stock went up, in an early burst of enthusiasm for=
 what would later be called meme stocks. Hertz thought, well, if our stock =
is going up, we should sell some stock, to raise money to pay off our credi=
tors =E2=80=94=C2=A0that is pretty much our duty as a company in bankruptcy=
. So it went to the bankruptcy court to ask for permission to sell stock, a=
nd the court was like =E2=80=9Csure I guess, good for creditors,=E2=80=9D a=
nd Hertz=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3048=
4592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjA=
tMDYtMjIvdGhlLWJlc3QtZnJhdWQtaXMtaW4tcGxhaW4tc2lnaHQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwNzIzX0=
1PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlc=
m09MjMwMjA3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB82d0d3=
1e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">launched an at-the-market offering</a> to sell up to=C2=A0$500=
 million of common stock to retail investors at the prevailing market price=
. The prospectus included a warning to the effect of (1) Hertz is bankrupt =
and (2) =E2=80=9Cwe expect that common stock holders would not receive a re=
covery=E2=80=9D in bankruptcy: basically, a warning that the stock was wort=
hless. But if people wanted to buy it, go ahead!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">People did want to buy it, at least a little b=
it, but the US Securities and Exchange Commission quickly called up Hertz t=
o say no, that=E2=80=99s not allowed, you can=E2=80=99t just sell stock to =
retail investors at market prices=C2=A0<em>when you are bankrupt</em>.=C2=
=A0=E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/304845=
92.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtM=
DYtMjIvdGhlLWJlc3QtZnJhdWQtaXMtaW4tcGxhaW4tc2lnaHQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwNzIzX01P=
TkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm0=
9MjMwMjA3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC82d0d31e=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">Fraud in plain sight</a>,=E2=80=9D a lawyer called it: Hertz knew=
 the stock was worthless and was, in some sense, tricking people into buyin=
g it, even though it did explicitly tell them that it was worthless. The of=
fering was quickly shut down. As it turns out the stock was not worthless, =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL25ld3NsZXR0ZXJzLzIwMjEtMDUtMTIvbW9uZ=
Xktc3R1ZmYtdGhlLWhlcnR6LWdhbWJsZXJzLXdlcmUtcmlnaHQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwNzIzX01P=
TkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm0=
9MjMwMjA3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB080499ca=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> Hertz exited bankruptcy</a> with significant recovery for the eq=
uity, and probably the SEC should have let it sell stock to retail investor=
s, but never mind.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bed Bath &amp; Beyond Inc. is not in bankruptc=
y, but it is about as close to bankruptcy as you can get, or was yesterday =
anyway.=C2=A0Here is a Bloomberg=C2=A0story from <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDEtMjcvYmVkLWJhdGgtYmV5b25kLWZhbHRlcnMtaW4=
tZWZmb3J0LXRvLWZpbmQtYnV5ZXItaW4tYmFua3J1cHRjeT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMjA3MjNfTU9ORV=
lTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yM=
zAyMDcmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3174ed4c" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">  two weeks ago</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bed Bath &amp; Beyond Inc.=E2=80=99s efforts t=
o find a buyer in bankruptcy have stalled, potentially putting the retailer=
 on a path toward liquidation as it faces a Chapter 11 filing, according to=
 people with knowledge of the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The retailer is preparing to file for bankrupt=
cy protection imminently, likely without a bidder in place for assets inclu=
ding its Buy Buy Baby brand, which is viewed by some as its most valuable c=
hain, said the people, who asked not to be named discussing private company=
 plans. They added that talks are ongoing and a buyer could still emerge.</=
p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s not just a story about Bed Bath=
 imminently filing for bankruptcy; that=E2=80=99s=C2=A0a story about Bed Ba=
th imminently filing for a <em>bad=C2=A0</em>bankruptcy, one in which there=
 are no bidders for its business and it just has to liquidate everything.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bed Bath has also been something of an on-and-=
off <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.25944=
8/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY25iYy5jb20vMjAyMy8wMS8xMS9iZWQtYmF0aC1iZXlvbmQtanVtcHMtN=
TBwZXJjZW50LXRvLWxlYWQtbGFzdC1nYXNwLXJhbGx5LWluLW1lbWUtc3RvY2tzLWFtYy1nYWlu=
cy0xNXBlcmNlbnQuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8752aa52" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> meme sto=
ck</a>, though. It is incredibly volatile. It is a recognizable retail bran=
d. It has heavy short interest. Ryan Cohen owned some stock for a while. It=
 did some <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592=
.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzg4NjE1OC8wMDA=
xMTkzMTI1MjIyNzE3NDUvZDM4NzYwM2Q0MjRiNS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3ce8f=
c3d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> at-the-market stock offerings</a> last year, raising money by=
 selling stock at market prices to mostly retail investors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But that was last October; by this month, Bed =
Bath was much closer to bankruptcy and it would have been pretty hard to do=
 that again. For one thing, meme-stock enthusiasm for Bed Bath has waned. F=
or another thing, we kind of know what the SEC thinks about all of this: Th=
ey don=E2=80=99t like it. If you do an at-the-market offering to retail inv=
estors that is like =E2=80=9Chey we=E2=80=99re basically bankrupt but if yo=
u give us a few hundred million dollars we=E2=80=99ll hand it over to credi=
tors, does that sound cool to you,=E2=80=9D the SEC will have objections, e=
ven if the retail investors are fine with it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, no one would object if Bed =
Bath was able to go out and sell stock to an institutional investor, a big =
hedge fund or other investment firm that knows what it is doing and can do =
its own due diligence.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem with that strategy is =E2=80=A6=C2=
=A0Bed Bath would have to find an investor like that? A deep-pocketed hedge=
 fund that wants to put a lot of money into a near-bankrupt company? Like, =
if you read that Bloomberg story two weeks ago, and you had a billion dolla=
rs, and you liked Bed Bath &amp; Beyond, what would you do about it? The mo=
st natural approach would=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>be to call up Bed Bath=E2=
=80=99s management and say =E2=80=9Chey, I have a billion dollars, will you=
 sell me a billion dollars=E2=80=99 worth of stock?=E2=80=9D The most natur=
al approach would be to call up Bed Bath=E2=80=99s management and say =E2=
=80=9Chey, I have a billion dollars, you have like <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi=
9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzg4NjE1OC8wMDAwODg2MTU4MjMwMDAwMjYvYmJieS0yMDIyM=
TEyNi5odG0jaTUxY2JlM2U2NjNjMjRhN2NiNDRiMmM0MjA1NDFlMzUyXzMx/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cBa0ea000a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> $2 billion of funded debt</a>, your unsecure=
d bonds are trading at <a href=3D"bbg://news/stories/RPPW5MT1UM0W" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
