<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Certificate of Dumb Investment</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the US, investments are mostly either=C2=A0=
<em>public=C2=A0</em>or=C2=A0<em>private</em>. Public investments are thing=
s like stocks that trade on the stock exchange, and anyone can buy them. Pr=
ivate investments are not traded on the stock exchange, and for the most pa=
rt you need to be an =E2=80=9Caccredited investor=E2=80=9D to buy them. =E2=
=80=9CAccredited investor=E2=80=9D is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9lZHVjYXRpb24=
vY2FwaXRhbHJhaXNpbmcvYnVpbGRpbmctYmxvY2tzL2FjY3JlZGl0ZWQtaW52ZXN0b3I/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB63388f8c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a legal category</a>; it is mainly a =
wealth/income=C2=A0test =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you make $200,000 a year or have =
at least $1 million of net worth, you=E2=80=99re probably accredited=C2=A0=
=E2=80=94=C2=A0though you can also be accredited if you have certain securi=
ties licenses.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The basic tension in the regulation of private=
 investments is that most of the best investments are private, and most of =
the worst investments are also private. US public companies tend to be larg=
e, mature, profitable, stable and well regulated; they rarely vanish overni=
ght due to fraud, but their fastest-growing days are generally behind them =
by the time they go public. The fast-growing exciting companies, the ones t=
hat will be the dominant public companies of the future, the next Googles o=
r Apples or whatever, are mostly private. Also though the unaudited frauds:=
 all private.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way that this tension plays out is that so=
metimes people argue that the accredited investor rules should be loosened,=
 so that more people can have access to fast-growing private companies, and=
 then other people argue that they should be tightened, so that fewer peopl=
e can have access to frauds. I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMDYtMTkvcHJpdmF0ZS1tYXJrZXRzLWNvdWxkLWJlLW1vcmUtcHVibGljP=
2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMDcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1u=
ZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIwNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB734bf975" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> have argued in the past</a>=C2=A0that e=
xpanding the accredited investor rules will=C2=A0<em>mostly=C2=A0</em>give =
people more access to frauds, because private investments are generally inv=
itation-only, and the next Google is not really looking to raise money from=
 just-barely-accredited retail investors.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But never mind that. I <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDktMjQvZWFybmluZy10aGUtcmlnaHQtdG8t=
Z2V0LXN3aW5kbGVkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMDcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWw=
mdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDIwNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZX=
lzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc16fff4f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> once suggested that</a=
>, if you really want to expand access to private markets, what you want is=
 a purely self-certified, opt-in accredited investor status. But what I spe=
cifically proposed is the following regulatory regime:</p>
<blockquote><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; marg=
in: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Anyone can invest all the=
y want in a diversified portfolio of approved investments (non-penny-stock =
public companies, mutual funds and exchange-traded funds with modest fees, =
insured bank accounts, etc.).</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Anyo=
ne can also invest in any other dumb investment; you just have to go to the=
 local office of the SEC and get a Certificate of Dumb Investment. (Anyone =
who sells dumb non-approved investments without requiring this certificate =
from buyers goes to prison.)=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;"=
>To get that certificate, you sign a form. The form is one page with a lot =
of white space. It says in very large letters: =E2=80=9CI want to buy a dum=
b investment. I understand that the person selling it will almost certainly=
 steal all my money, and that I would almost certainly be better off just b=
uying index funds, but I want to do this dumb thing anyway. I agree that I =
will never, under any circumstances, complain to anyone when this investmen=
t inevitably goes wrong. I understand that violating this agreement is a fe=
lony.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then you take the f=
orm to an SEC employee, who slaps you hard across the face and says =E2=80=
=9Creally???=E2=80=9D And if you reply =E2=80=9Cyes really=E2=80=9D then sh=
e gives you the certificate.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Then =
you bring the certificate to the seller and you can buy whatever dumb thing=
 he=C2=A0is selling.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If an article=
 ever appears in the Wall Street Journal in which you (or your lawyer) are =
quoted saying that you were just a simple dentist, didn=E2=80=99t understan=
d what you were buying and=C2=A0were swindled by the seller=E2=80=99s flash=
y sales pitch, then=C2=A0<em>you</em>=C2=A0go to prison.</li>
</ol></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I feel like a lot of people agree with the bas=
ic idea of =E2=80=9Canyone should be allowed to self-certify that they are =
accredited and then invest in whatever they want,=E2=80=9D=C2=A0but without=
 the=C2=A0<em>essential=C2=A0</em>elements of my proposal, which are (1) th=
e form being very clear about what a bad idea it is, (2) the slapping, and =
(3) no complaining, ever.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For instance, now that Republicans are in char=
ge of the US House of Representatives, there is a <a href=3D"https://link.m=
ail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly9maW5hbmNpYWxzZXJ=
2aWNlcy5ob3VzZS5nb3YvdXBsb2FkZWRmaWxlcy9hY2NyZWRpdGVkX2ludmVzdG9yX3NlbGYtY2=
VydGlmaWNhdGlvbl9hY3QucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB167c88db" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> prop=
osed bill</a> =E2=80=9Cto amend the Securities Act of 1933 to permit indivi=
duals to self-certify as an accredited investor=E2=80=9D (<a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30484592.259448/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGV=
yLmNvbS9iYW5rX3JlZy9zdGF0dXMvMTYyMTgyNzg0MTU5MDcxMDI3NA/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cBb21ec00f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">pointed out</a> by Bank Reg Blog on Twitter). It=E2=
=80=99s short; the proposal is that anyone can be accredited with respect t=
o any particular investment if she =E2=80=9Chas self-certified to the issue=
r that=C2=A0the individual understands the risks of investment in private i=
ssuers, using such form as the=C2=A0Commission shall establish, by rule, bu=
t which form may not be longer than 2 pages in length.=E2=80=9D I appreciat=
e the page limit, though, again,=C2=A0<em>my=C2=A0</em>form would be one pa=
ge.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I just worry that people who like this idea li=
ke it for the wrong reasons. Like here is the certificate that I worry peop=
le will draft:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>SELF-CERTIFICATION OF SOPHISTICATION</=
strong></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I represent that I am financially sophisticate=
d and=C2=A0well qualified to access and evaluate investments that are open =
only to accredited investors. I acknowledge that I am good at evaluating in=
vestments, and that I have done my own research and due diligence to evalua=
te this one. I am a big boy or girl. I acknowledge that this is an exclusiv=
e high-return investment open only to the most sophisticated investors and =
that, like all such investments, it carries certain risks, including the ri=
sk of total loss. But as a bold and sophisticated investor I have a high to=
lerance for the risks that accompany high expected returns. Let's go!</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can write stuff like that, stuff that look=
s to a lawyer like an acknowledgement of risks but that looks to a human li=
ke an=C2=A0<em>advertisement</em>. Who wouldn=E2=80=99t want to sign that? =
No, my certificate would look like this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>CERTIFICATE OF DUMB INVESTMENT</strong=
></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I acknowledge that I am an idiot. I acknowledg=
e that I have been swindled into making this investment by someone who is s=
marter than me and who wants to take my money, and I acknowledge that they =
will almost certainly take all of it and I will get none of it back. I here=
by kiss all my money goodbye.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Do those two versions mean the same thing? Kin=
d of! But you want it to be clear!</p>
